    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is assessed as low impact given the deterministic quasi-static loading regime and consistency with FDA-accepted ASTM F1717 practice. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
